  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 220°C (425°F).",
    "In a mixing bowl, combine the lean beef mince, Thai chilli jam, garlic, salt, black pepper, lime juice, buckwheat flour, egg, and a sprinkle of chopped parsley and mint leaves. Mix well until just combined.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a slate-tile baking dish and cook for 15 minutes. ",
    "After 15 minutes, brush the glaze (equal parts honey and soy sauce) over the top of the mixture and return to the oven for a further 5-7 minutes.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving with a dollop of Greek yogurt and additional chopped scotch bonnet peppers (if desired).",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
